  "elapsed_s": 2.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that she forgot all her catechism, and that she forgot all of her prayers, and would they take her in?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And sure enough, they took her in.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they did enter into refreshing her memory to such an extent that she became a very, very good Catholic, an honest-to-goodness believing Catholic.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I, in the meantime, roomed with a family, a non-Jewish family, of course, and was working.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One of the things that I struck a deal with the Mother Superior for is that since there was an orphanage there of different ages, of girls of different ages, and they don't have education, would she permit me to come once a week on Sunday-- I posed as my sister's aunt-- to teach them something?",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that would give me contact with my sister.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And indeed, I would come there every Sunday, and I would teach the girls.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I would sort of steal myself away for a few moments with her, and she would tell me a few things about her life and how she felt and all that.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In the meantime, while I was with my family, I had to play a very good Catholic as well, and I was going with them to mass every, every Sunday.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was really integrated into their lifestyle so that I wouldn't act any differently from the way they were acting.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
